[u'Al Jazeera PR', u'Home', u'About', u'Awards', u'Contact Us', u'Archive', u'Al Jazeera PR', u'\u0647\u0646\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u064a\u0631\u0629', u'Search', u'Senior Hamas leader speaks to Al Jazeera on moving the US embassy to Jerusalem', u'Reveals Hamas will be releasing a new\ncharter \u201cvery soon\u201d that addresses anti-Semitic statements in their 1988\noriginal charter', u'\xa0Says it\u2019s \u201cinaccurate\u201d to suggest Hamas\nsupports a two-state solution, but says they support a \u201cPalestinian state on the\nlines of 4', u'th', u'Supports the newly announced unity\ngovernment with rival faction Fatah: \u201cThe international community will not\nsupport us unless we\u2019re united\u201d', u'Warns U.S. President Donald Trump not to\nadd \u201cmore oil to the fire\u201d by moving the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv\nto Jerusalem.', u'\xa0', u'(Washington,\nD.C. \u2013 25', u'th', u', January)', u'UpFron', u't', u', Osama Hamdan, a senior leader of Hamas, revealed that the group is\nworking on a new charter which includes addressing\nwidely criticised anti-Semitic statements in\nthe [1988] original. \xa0', u'\u201cWe\nwill have a clear political document, which is supposed to be in the near\nfuture, clarifying all those points,\u201d Hamadan told ', u'UpFront', u'\u201cYou will find in this document\nclear words that we against the Zionists, against the occupation of our lands\nand we will resist the occupiers, whoever they were. And we are not against\nanyone regarding to this religion or to his race,\u201d Hamdan said. ', u'When asked about a\ntimeframe for the new charter, Hamdan said it would be released \u201cvery soon\u201d.', u'Hamdan also commented\non his organisation\u2019s current stance on a two-state solution with\nIsrael.\xa0\u201cWe want to build a Palestinian state on the lines of\nthe 4', u'th', u'However, when pressed\nto further clarify if that meant Hamas supports a\ntwo-state solution, Hamdan said that \u201cwould be\ninaccurate\u201d. ', u'\u201cYou can call it\nwhatever you want, but this is what we accept. Nothing more than this, nothing\nless than this,\u201d he added.', u'On the issue of the\nnewly announced unity government with rival Palestinian group Fatah, Hamdan\noffered his full support. \u201cWe need\u2026 a national unity government,\u201d he said. \u201cIsraelis now are taking over the land\nby the settlements. The region is unstable.\u201d ', u'\u201cThe international\ncommunity is not willing to help the Palestinians unless they are united,\u201d\nhe added. \xa0', u'During the interview,\nHamdan was also asked how he believes new U.S. President Donald Trump\u2019s support\nof Israel and plans to move the U.S. embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem might\nimpact the region.', u'\u201c[Trump] has\nto make a choice whether he wants to create peace in the region or he wants to\nadd more oil on the\nfire,\u201d he said. ', u'\u201cPalestinians will\nnot accept to abandon Jerusalem, they will not accept to abandon their rights,\u201d he added. \xa0', u'Asked whether or not the embassy moving to Jerusalem would lead to renewed\nviolence, Hamdan said: \u201cI don\u2019t accept the idea of having violence from the\nPalestinian side.\u201d', u'\u201cNow if there was\nchanges or the United States administration try to make a change in the status\nof Jerusalem, of course that will mean an action from the Palestinian side and\nno one can control that,\u201d he added. \xa0', u'He also defended his\norganisation\u2019s past use of suicide attacks across the Green Line, against\nIsraeli targets, asking, \u201cWhat\u2019s the problem in that: the bombs or the suicide\nactions?\u201d \u2013 He made a comparison with Israeli rockets against Palestinian homes\nand markets. ', u'\u201cAs Palestinians we\ndon\u2019t have\u2026\xa0 tanks\u2026so we use what we have,\u201d he added. \xa0', u'###', u'Note\nto Editors', u'\xb7\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\xa0\nThis ', u'UpFront', u'\xb7\xa0\xa0\xa